    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 1 vs. required Gradation 2) is accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 mandates quasi-static testing and rate sensitivity for Ti-6Al-4V constructs at quasi-static rates is well-characterized in the published literature. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% across all 11 specimens and both laboratories. The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible for the stated COU.",
